Hollywood newcomer @sarahyarkin isn’t your typical “coming-of-age” movie actress. Instead, she’s spent the last couple of years building a reputation for herself as an all around on-screen badass. 

Now she portrays the beatnik, feisty teenage ghost "Rhonda" new Paramount+ YA series School Spirits, who is stuck in the afterlife after being murdered by her guidance counselor in 1963.

1883 Magazine chats with Yarkin about the playing high school outcast ghost Rhonda, starring in a legendary horror reboot, and her approach to channeling vulnerability in songwriting.
